Extra exercises

Gapminder

We will investigate the gapminder dataset using ggplot2 and dplyr. If you have followed our ‘crash-course’ these data should be familiar to you. In brief, these data give various indicator variables for different countries around the world (life expectancy, population and Gross Domestic Product). A subset of this large dataset are available in the gapminder package, but we have saved these data as a .csv file to demonstrate how to import data into R.

library(dplyr)
gapminder <- read.csv("gapminder.csv") %>% tbl_df
gapminder

As an example of the ‘canvas-model’ of base graphics we saw how to plot the relationship between life expectancy and gdp for african and european countries on the same graph using points.
